The last execution in [[Armenia]] took place on the 30 August 1991; it was carried out [[execution by shooting|by a single bullet]]. [[Death penalty]] remained a legal punishment for [[murder]], [[treason]], and serious crimes of a military nature, until its abolition in 2003. The death penalty was replaced with [[life imprisonment]] for all crimes.

In 2003 Armenia also ratified the Protocol No. 6 to the [[European Convention on Human Rights]] (the Protocol allows countries to retain death penalty for serious wartime crimes).<ref>[http://conventions.coe.int/Treaty/Commun/ChercheSig.asp?NT=114&CM=8&DF=3/20/2009&CL=ENG Protocol No. 6 to the Convention for the Protection of Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms concerning the Abolition of the Death Penalty CETS No.: 114; status as of 20/3/2009]</ref> Protocol No. 13 (concerning abolition of the death penalty under all circumstances) was signed in 2006; however, as of January 2008 Armenia has not ratified it.<ref>[http://conventions.coe.int/Treaty/Commun/ChercheSig.asp?NT=187&CM=8&DF=3/20/2009&CL=ENG Protocol No. 13 to the Convention for the Protection of Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms, concerning the abolition of the death penalty in all circumstances CETS No.: 187; status as of 20/3/2009]</ref>

