'''Lachik''' is a [[Kachin people|Kachin]] sub-tribe. It has its own language/dialect. The sub-tribes are [[Nung Rawang|Rawang]], the [[Lisu people|Lisu]], the [[Zaiwa]], the Lashi/Lachik, the Lawngwaw and [[Jingpo people|Jingpo]]. A group of seven sub-tribes call Kachin (Wunhpawng).

The majority of Lachik people live in northern [[Burma]]'s Kachin State and bordering areas between [[Myanmar]] and [[China]]. 

==Dress==
Lachik costumes differ from other Kachin sub-tribes and have specific meaning.

