{{Infobox recurring event | name = Monmouth Women's Festival | logo = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | date = | begins = | ends = | frequency = Annual | location = [[Monmouth]], Wales | years_active = Since 2004<!--Date of the first occurrence--> | first = | last = | participants = | attendance = | organised = | website = {{URL|www.monmouthwomensfestival.com}} | footnotes = }} '''Monmouth Women's Festival''' is an annual event in [[Monmouth]], Wales, focusing on issues of interest to women. It is a not-for-profit cultural festival including workshops, talks and other events, and is organised by a small committee of volunteers.
The 2012 festival, the ninth in the event's history, took place between 2–18 March. Guest speakers included [[Julia Donaldson]], [[Erin Pizzey]] and [[Jennie Bond]].
{{Quote|To mark [[International Women's Day]] in Monmouth through the organising of the events for the community, by raising awareness of the issues facing women both locally, internationally and across all races and cultures, and by celebrating women’s achievements.}}
