'''Wolofal''' is a derivation of the [[Arabic script]] for writing the [[Wolof language]]. It is basically the name of a [[West Africa]]n [[Ajami script]] as used for that language.
Wolofal was the first script for writing Wolof language. Although the Latin alphabet is the official script of the language in today's Senegal, Wolofal is still used by many people as a symbol of Islamic Wolof culture.{{Citation needed|date=July 2011}}
